<!DOCTYPE html> - tells the browser what version of html the code was written in, this is for html 5
<html lang="en"> - language of the text content within the website
  <head> - doesn't include any content but provides info for the browser
    <meta charset="UTF-8"> - what character set you're using, some won't allow emojis etc
    <title>My Document</title> - used to explain what the website is, company name etc
  </head>
  
  <body> - where all the content of the website goes
  
  </body>
</html>
